        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh hardens channel setup selection projection: setup picker rows are copied through bounded readers before visibility checks, sorting, hint lookup, and contribution construction, so one unreadable channel setup row does not hide healthy setup choices\n- rebased over the latest provider discovery runtime changes and preserved both paths: unreadable discovery-entry providers are isolated, mixed static/runtime manifest catalog coverage stays intact, and failed projection plugins remain in scoped fallback loads beside runtime manifest catalog plugins\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `b7a49153949`, proven on `origin/main` at `da5d1a62155e3344dc70c09becde4a8e88544dc7`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 2 files passed, 43 tests passed\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 1 file passed, 31 tests passed after the autoreview follow-up\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/flows/channel-setup.status.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.test.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts src/plugins/provider-plugin-projection.ts src/plugins/providers.runtime.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/flows/channel-setup.status.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.test.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts src/plugins/provider-plugin-projection.ts src/plugins/providers.runtime.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean after adding the provider-discovery fallback/runtime-manifest regression\n- `OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run -provider blacksmith-testbox -shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`: blocked before remote execution because Blacksmith is not authenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required)\n- scrubbed touched files/spec/PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, provider/runtime/channel/plugin registry projections, model/provider install catalog projections, provider discovery projection, web search install catalog projection, model picker provider catalog projection, web search setup provider projection, provider model-picker flow projection, provider setup flow projection, provider runtime hook-ref projection, and channel setup selection projection no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable env vars, unreadable install/provider metadata, unreadable catalog hooks, unreadable setup provider rows, unreadable setup choices, unreadable channel setup rows, or unreadable model-picker contribution rows while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, based on `origin/main` at `da5d1a62155e3344dc70c09becde4a8e88544dc7`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: after the channel setup selection slice, provider-discovery conflict resolution, and fallback follow-up, ran focused Vitest for channel setup status and provider discovery runtime, formatting, linting, commit diff check, synthetic/private-name scrub, autoreview on the actual fallback fix, and attempted the Blacksmith-backed changed gate listed in Verification.\n\nEvidence after fix: `channel-setup.status.test.ts` seeds an unreadable `fuzzplugin` setup entry while proving the healthy `mockplugin` setup choice remains visible. `provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts` covers unreadable discovery-entry providers, manifest catalog preservation beside fallback loads, entries-only completeness for mixed static/runtime catalogs, and the autoreview-found case where failed projection plugins must stay in fallback loading beside runtime manifest catalog plugins.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed channel setup metadata no longer aborts setup contribution construction before healthy rows are reached; malformed provider discovery entries no longer drop healthy provider rows or omit required fallback full-load plugin ids when runtime manifest catalog plugins are also involved.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate did not run because the local Blacksmith CLI is unauthenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required). AWS Crabbox broad gate was not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted channel-setup/provider-discovery/provider-flow/provider-runtime surfaces plus formatter/lint/autoreview checks.\n",
